<section class="section" id="modules">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label reveal">Development Lego</div>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Modules that snap together.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub reveal">Each module implements a standard interface. The kernel discovers capabilities automatically. Build your own or use the ones that ship with Devify.</p>

    <div class="modules-grid reveal-stagger">
      <div class="module-card reveal">
        <div class="module-header">
          <span class="module-name">auth</span>
          <span class="module-badge core">CORE</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>User registration, login, logout</li>
          <li>Password reset flow</li>
          <li>Session or JWT (configurable)</li>
          <li>argon2id password hashing</li>
          <li>RequireAuth / RequireGuest middleware</li>
          <li>UserService exported for other modules</li>
          <li>Events: UserRegistered, UserLoggedIn</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="module-card reveal">
        <div class="module-header">
          <span class="module-name">rbac</span>
          <span class="module-badge core">CORE</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Roles and permissions management</li>
          <li>RequireRole / RequirePermission middleware</li>
          <li>Auto-assigns default role on registration</li>
          <li>Depends on auth via DI (not imports)</li>
          <li>Subscribes to auth events via EventBus</li>
          <li>Own database schema, own migrations</li>
          <li>CLI: devify rbac:assign-role</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="module-card reveal">
        <div class="module-header">
          <span class="module-name">tenant</span>
          <span class="module-badge core">CORE</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Multi-tenancy: orgs &amp; workspaces</li>
          <li>Membership with scoped roles</li>
          <li>Invite flow with token-based accept</li>
          <li>Header / subdomain / path resolution</li>
          <li>Auto-create personal tenant on signup</li>
          <li>ResolveTenant / RequireTenant middleware</li>
          <li>CLI: devify tenant:list, tenant:create</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="module-card custom reveal">
        <div class="module-header">
          <span class="module-name">your-module</span>
          <span class="module-badge ext">CUSTOM</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Scaffold in seconds with the CLI</li>
          <li>Pick capabilities: routes, migrations, events</li>
          <li>Own database schema, own views</li>
          <li>Expose services for other modules via DI</li>
          <li>Register CLI subcommands</li>
          <li>Add scheduled tasks</li>
          <li>Publish as a Go package for others</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
